args: Trying to help with chores isn't\ngoing well for me at all.
And yet, I don't want to make everyone\nchange their ways to accommodate me.
There MUST be something I can do.
That sounded like it came from\nthe courtyard.
Oh man, there's no WAY I'm gonna\never find that now...
Luca? Why are you holding your head\nin your hands like that?
Hey, Felicia. Feel like laughing\nlike an idiot AT an idiot?
What? I would never laugh at you, Luca!\nI'm sure it's nothing as bad as all that.
Oh, but it is. It most certainly is.\nSo go on! Laugh! Laugh at me!\nLAUGH, DAMN YOU! LAAAAUGH!
Eeek! Y-you're scaring me, Luca!\nJust calm down and tell me what's wrong.
Oh, I'll tell you what's wrong...
The tablecloth I was drying got\nblown away by the wind!
It was Cleo's favorite, too—which means\nshe's gonna skin me alive when she\nfinds out about it.
Oh dear. That IS a problem.
Oh, I have an idea! In fact,\nwhy don't you leave this to me?
Er, are you sure about this...?
Now that you mention it, I don't think\nshe was at breakfast this morning.
She's not one for oversleeping.\nMaybe she isn't feeling well.
That's a worrying thought.\nShould I go check on her?
You look restless, Luca. Everything okay?
Huh?! Oh, um, I'm just worried about\nFelicia! That's all. ...Really.
You have a lean and guilty look about you,\nsir. What do you know?
M-me? Guilty? Ha ha ha! Don't be silly!\nI'm just going to...go...check up on her.
If Felicia is unwell, someone considerate\nto her needs should be the one to see her.
R-right! Which is why a fellow sylvan like\nme is just the fellow to go.
Are those not both points in favor\nof CLEO going?
Why do I get the feeling you're trying to\nkeep me away from Felicia?
Um... Weeeell... See, the truth is...
What have you been doing holed up\nin your room all this time, Felicia?
I'm sorry. I got so engrossed in making\nthis that I lost track of time.
It's lovely. Did you really make this?
I've always enjoyed working with lace.
At first I used to just make dance outfits,\nbut soon I could make lots of other things.
What inspired you to make this?
Well, yesterday the tablecloth\nin the laundry got—
Er...I mean...I made this on a whim!\nYep! Toootal whimsy.
It certainly has nothing to do with Luca\nletting the other one get blown away.
Ack! I'm sorry! It just slipped out!
Felicia really cannot tell a lie.\nOr even step carefully around one.
I see what's going on here, Luca.
*sigh* Yes, it was me. I'm sorry.
I was so very fond of that tablecloth.
And yet, I can see myself growing\njust as fond of this one.
Felicia has replaced what was lost,\nso I will let you off—THIS time.
Whew! You saved me big time, Felicia.
*sigh*\nIn any case, it's time for lunch.
Let's have our first meal using\nthis wonderful tablecloth.
I'm guessing you must be hungry\nafter all that sewing, Felicia.
All's well that ends well, then.\nNow let's dig in!
